    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ariadne-entry\"><p><strong>Source:</strong> Ariadne's Book of Legends - Alpha v1.2, p. 123.</p><p>Abjure</p><p>10th-level abjuration</p><p>Classes: Sorcerer, Wizard Casting Time: 1 reaction, which you take when a creature you can see within 120 feet of you casts a spell Range: 120 feet Components: V, S, M (a platinum symbol of the Abjuration school worth at least 1.000 GP) Duration: Instantaneous</p><p>With a powerful word of abjuration, you interrupt the casting of a spell. If the creature is casting a spell of 9thlevel or lower, it fails and has no effect. The creature must then make a Charisma saving throw. On a success, it cannot cast spells of the same school of magic as the interrupted spell for the next 24 hours. On a failed save, the target’s magical conduits decompose, causing them to take 10d10 force damage and becoming unable to cast spells. The target’s conduits can be restored by a casting of Regenerate or similar magic.</p><p>If you use this spell against a creature that is casting a 10th-level spell, you must make a spellcasting ability contest against them. If you succeed, they suffer the spell’s effects as normal. If you fail, Abjure has no effect.</p></div>",
